laliga = as.tbl(spain)
blaliga = rbind(laliga %>% select(Date, Season, team = home, opp = visitor, GF = hgoal, GA = vgoal), laliga %>% select(Date, Season, team = visitor, opp = home, GF = vgoal, GA = hgoal)) %>% arrange(Date)
rankings = blaliga %>% mutate(GD = GF - GA) %>% group_by(team, Season) %>% summarize(
            gp = n(), 
            gf = sum(GF), 
            ga = sum(GA), 
            gd = sum(GD),
            w = sum(GD > 0),
            d = sum(GD == 0),
            l = sum(GD < 0)
  ) %>% 
  mutate(points = d + w * 3) %>%
  arrange(Season, desc(points)) %>% 
  group_by(Season) %>% 
  mutate(rank = rank(-points*777777 - gd*777 - gf) %>% as.integer())

champions = rankings %>% select(Season,points,team,rank) %>% group_by(Season) %>%  filter(rank == 1)
champions_count = champions %>% group_by(team) %>% summarise(count = n()) %>% arrange(desc(count))
highchart() %>% hc_chart(type = "column") %>% hc_title(text = "Number of championships") %>% hc_xAxis(categories = champions_count$team) %>% hc_add_series(champions_count$count)
ggplot(data = champions_count, aes(x = reorder(team, -count), y = count)) + geom_bar(width = 0.5, stat="identity") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90)) + xlab("Team") + ylab("Number of champhions")

consecutive = blaliga %>% mutate(win = (GF > GA), lose = (GF < GA), draw = (GF == GA))
teams_best = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 4))
teams_current = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 4))

colnames(teams_best) <- c("name","w","d","l")
colnames(teams_current) <- c("name","w","d","l")

consecutive = consecutive %>% select(Date ,Season, team, win, lose, draw)

win_strike = function(team_seq){
  cur_win = 0
  max_win = 0
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(team_seq))){
    if(team_seq[[i,"win"]]){
      cur_win = cur_win + 1
      max_win = max(cur_win, max_win)
    }
    else{
      cur_win = 0
    }
  }
  return (max_win)
}

win_sequence = consecutive %>% group_by(team) %>% do(data.frame(win_numbers = win_strike(.))) %>% arrange(desc(win_numbers))
mx = max(win_sequence$win_numbers)
win_sequence = win_sequence %>% filter(win_numbers == mx)
cat("Longest winning strike is for :",win_sequence$team,"\n")
## Longest winning strike is for : FC Barcelona Real Madrid
cat("Number of games :",win_sequence$win_numbers,"\n")
## Number of games : 16 16
lose_strike = function(team_seq){
  cur_lose = 0
  max_lose = 0
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(team_seq))){
    if(team_seq[[i,"lose"]]){
      cur_lose = cur_lose + 1
      max_lose = max(cur_lose, max_lose)
    }
    else{
      cur_lose = 0
    }
  }
  return (max_lose)
}

lose_sequence = consecutive %>% group_by(team) %>% do(data.frame(lose_numbers = lose_strike(.))) %>% arrange(desc(lose_numbers))
mx = max(lose_sequence$lose_numbers)
lose_sequence = lose_sequence %>% filter(lose_numbers == mx)

cat("Number of games :",lose_sequence$lose_numbers,"\n")

no_lose_strike = function(team_seq){
  cur_no_lose = 0
  max_no_lose = 0
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(team_seq))){
    if(team_seq[[i,"lose"]]){
      cur_no_lose = 0
    }
    else{
      cur_no_lose = cur_no_lose + 1
      max_no_lose = max(cur_no_lose, max_no_lose)
    }
  }
  return (max_no_lose)
}

no_lose_sequence = consecutive %>% group_by(team) %>% do(data.frame(no_lose_numbers = no_lose_strike(.))) %>% arrange(desc(no_lose_numbers))
mx = max(no_lose_sequence$no_lose_numbers)
no_lose_sequence = no_lose_sequence %>% filter(no_lose_numbers == mx)
cat("Longest without losing strike is for :",no_lose_sequence$team,"\n")
## Longest without losing strike is for : Real Sociedad
cat("Number of games :",no_lose_sequence$no_lose_numbers,"\n")
## Number of games : 38
